With malle, quam is more often omitted than expressed, but when it is expressed‚ and is preceded by an infinitive depending on malle, an infinitive also usually follows. This is the almost uniform practice of the whole period. Still, there are some exceptions: Cf. Plaut. As. 121: Morire sese misere mavolet quam non perfeetum reddat quod promiserit. Another interesting use of the subjunctive with velle, which has not received the attention it deserves, is that which is found with considerable frequency in the answers to questions of the type of quid vis? or numquid vis. These answers appear in several forms. Sometimes the response is not a direct one, the person addressed replying with a statement2 or with another question ²³.
